  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nBefore merging https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/1123, we used to have flickering sync tests:\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/runs/2862090073?check_suite_focus=true\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/runs/2861968072?check_suite_focus=true\r\n\r\nThe most likely cause to this is starting docker-compose multiple times, which I have experienced while developing locally.\r\n\r\nAs follow ups, the best course of action would be to\r\n1. Fix the root cause of verifier mismatches that's forcing us to do this test in a separate workflow\r\n2. Bring the verifier up with the rest of the stack instead of individually during this test, to fix flakiness\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSee linked CI failures above.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nSync tests only fail when a change causes a state root divergence, not randomly. \r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThis is also related to mismatched verifier state roots.\r\n",
